Node.Notes: Likely someone who has either been kicked out of community or has voluntarily withdrawn from it.
Literally, "his neighbor," probably an accuser in a cross-examination in this setting.
Probably something like an offended brother [is more inaccessible] than a fortified city."
Uncertain what "a man of friends to be broken up" means. Perhaps false friends are intended," so that a man with (false) friends [is destined] to be ruined."
